<TITLE> Govt approves VoIP policy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 14 (bdnews24.com)  The interim cabinet has approved a policy on VoIP to boost "the economy through the highest use of submarine cable capacity", the government said in a statement Saturday. The policy has been named ILDTS Policy 2007 or International Long Distance Telecommunication Services Policy, the statement said. At the meeting, Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission chairman Manzurul Alam gave a presentation on the policy on voice over internet protocol, which means the routing of voice conversations over the internet or through any other IP-based network. The cabinet at a meeting Saturday approved the memorandum and articles of association of Bangladesh Airlines Limited in line with the 1994 Companies Act as part of the process of converting the national flag carrier into a public limited company. The cabinet also approved the draft of Bangladesh Flag Vessels (Protection) Ordinance (Amended) 2007 at the meeting, chaired by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed. bdnews
